Time slows down in a photograph. It’s a part of why I love this craft. When I look back, there’s so many little moments I can never fully appreciate until I sit with the image. This half above / half below water shot was something we dreamt about before ever traveling to Mallorca. We wanted to shoot some deep water soloing but also bring to life the beauty of the ocean. I borrowed a large dome port to create this shot. The jelly fish just so happened to drift in for added affect hahah.

